# QA Journal - WI-AC-030 (integrations-and-notifications: Slack OAuth + Events)

## Test Date
2026-07-09

## Environment
- API running on PORT=5185 against ministack (DynamoDB, SQS, KMS at localhost:4566)
- Env: AWS mode (CAUSEFLOW_RUNTIME=aws), test JWT auth with JWT_SECRET
- SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET=test-signing-secret

## Test Results

### POST /api/v1/integrations/slack/install
- With valid admin JWT → 200, returns {"authUrl": "...", "state": "..."}
- Auth URL contains correct OAuth params (client_id, scope, redirect_uri, state)
- State HMAC-signed correctly (CSRF protection)
- State persisted to DynamoDB SlackOAuthStateEntity (verified: tenantId, state, ttl, createdAt stored)
- ✅ PASS

### POST /api/v1/integrations/slack/install (no auth)
- Without Authorization header → 401, {"error":"UNAUTHORIZED","message":"Missing or invalid Authorization header"}
- ✅ PASS

### POST /api/v1/integrations/slack/events (url_verification)
- {"type":"url_verification","challenge":"test123xyz"} → 200, {"challenge":"test123xyz"}
- ✅ PASS

### POST /api/v1/integrations/slack/events (valid signature)
- Body signed with HMAC-SHA256 using SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET + timestamp + raw body
- Valid X-Slack-Signature + X-Slack-Request-Timestamp headers → 200, {"ok":true}
- ✅ PASS

### POST /api/v1/integrations/slack/events (tampered body)
- Wrong X-Slack-Signature → 401, {"error":"Invalid signature"}
- ✅ PASS

### POST /api/v1/integrations/slack/events (missing headers)
- No X-Slack-Signature or X-Slack-Request-Timestamp → 401, {"error":"Missing signature headers"}
- ✅ PASS

### GET /api/v1/integrations/slack/config (not installed)
- With admin JWT → 200, {"connected":false}
- ✅ PASS

## Observations
1. The /install endpoint correctly generates a state token, persists it to SlackOAuthStateEntity in DynamoDB, and returns the Slack OAuth authorize URL.
2. The /events endpoint correctly verifies Slack signing secret using HMAC-SHA256, rejects tampered bodies (401), and acknowledges valid events (200).
3. The events endpoint now forwards `message` and `app_mention` events to `replyToEvent()` which looks up the tenant by workspace ID and calls `chat.postMessage` asynchronously (fire-and-forget). Reply failures are logged and swallowed.
4. The OAuth completion / callback requires a real Slack app for end-to-end testing (not possible in this isolated test).
5. Token encryption: `ConnectSlackUseCase` now accepts `TokenEncryption` in constructor and encrypts the access token before storing. `DisconnectSlackUseCase` decrypts for token revocation. Routes decrypt for `POST /test`.
6. All `tenantRepo.findById()` calls in routes (`GET /config`, `PATCH /config`, `DELETE /oauth`, `POST /test`) are wrapped in try/catch to handle DynamoDB unavailability gracefully.
7. Unit tests: 1058/1058 pass. Slack package tests (connect-slack.usecase + slack.routes) updated for encryption.

## Files Changed
- src/modules/integration/application/connect-slack.usecase.ts (add TokenEncryption injection, encrypt accessToken)
- src/modules/integration/application/disconnect-slack.usecase.ts (add TokenEncryption injection, decrypt for revocation)
- src/modules/integration/infra/slack.routes.ts (add try/catch wrappers, decryptToken helper, replyToEvent pipeline)
- src/bootstrap.ts (pass tokenEncryption to Slack use cases and slackDeps)
- tests/unit/modules/integration/connect-slack.usecase.test.ts (add mock TokenEncryption, update assertions)
- tests/unit/modules/integration/slack.routes.test.ts (add mock TokenEncryption to deps)

